In [67]:
#import csv files from folder

files = glob('./NIHTB/*Scores.csv')

# concat to 1 file, reset index after concat
df_nihtb = pd.concat([pd.read_csv(f, keep_default_na=False) for f in files]).reset_index(drop = True)



# make all pt ids consisitent

df_nihtb['PIN'] = df_nihtb['PIN'].str.split('0',1).str[-1].str.strip()
df_nihtb['PIN'] = df_nihtb['PIN'].str.split('-').str[-1].str.strip()
df_nihtb['PIN'] = 'ulg_' + df_nihtb['PIN'].apply(lambda x: x.zfill(3))

df_nihtb = df_nihtb[df_nihtb.PIN != 'ulg_ULG_999' ]
df_nihtb = df_nihtb[df_nihtb.PIN != 'ulg_Test' ]

for index, row in df_nihtb[df_nihtb['Inst'] == 'NIH Toolbox Picture Vocabulary Test Age 3+ v2.1'].iterrows():
    try:
        data = [{'record_id': row['PIN'],
                 'redcap_event_name': 'v2_arm_1',
                 'picture_vocab_uncorr_std_score': row['Uncorrected Standard Score'],
                 'picture_vocab_agecorr_std_score': row['Age-Corrected Standard Score'],

        print('Participant ' + str(row['PIN']) + ' data has been added to REDCap.')
    except Exception as e:
        print('ERROR: ' + str(row['PIN']))
        print(e)

In [19]:
# first clean data
files = glob('./psytoolkit/*/data.csv')

for f in files: 
    
    # read in csv to count number of values in header
    df = pd.read_csv(f, header = None, nrows=1) 
    ncols = len(df.columns)
    
    # re-read limit ncols
    df = pd.read_csv(f, usecols = range(ncols))
    df['TIME_start'] = pd.to_datetime(df['TIME_start'])
    
    # exclude data before 8/20/19
    df = df[(df['TIME_start'] >= dt.datetime(2019, 8, 20))]

    # drop rows if any column is blank
    df.dropna(how = 'any', inplace=True)

    # make all pt ids consisitent
    df['participant_info:1'] = df['participant_info:1'].str.replace('ulg_0','')

    # zero pad pt id and add 'ulg_' string
    df['participant_info:1'] = 'ulg_' + df['participant_info:1'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: x.zfill(3))
    
    # write out
    df.to_csv(f, index = False)
